        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "A new option should be added which allows Zend_Translate to load a language when it's needed.\n\nNow all languages have to be loaded in memory, which makes it consume much memory if you are having much translations.\n\nWith this option \"reducememory\" Zend_Translate would first load only which languages are avaiable and check if the files are properly or defect.\n\nAs soon as a translation occurs the expected language will be loaded.\nInternally the list of known languages makes it possible to act as it is done now.\n\nThe loading of the language afterwards mean\n*) Only one language in memory\n*) Needs more time on the first translation of a language as all needed sources are loaded\n\nMost applications would probably only use one or two of multiple languages so the benefit is given on a real multi-lingual application."
        },
